title: 'Series' object has no attribute 'nonzero'

labels.name: usage exception
labels.description: Exception during a SSE function call from Qlik

body:
**Function**
Pytools.Prophet

**Describe the bug**
I have created virtual environment in Anaconda and installed all the required packages as per init file. After that I am able to start the project as well and when I start QlikSense desktop it shows adding all the capabilities. Issue is when I open any of the apps like Forecasting and other I am getting few errors like "'Series' object has no attribute 'nonzero'" in the Forecasting app and " No such file or directory: '..\\models\\NoShow-RF.joblib'" while using ML Predictions app.

**Full error message from Python**
Provide full stack trace for the error.
If using `Qlik-Py-Start` you can provide screenshots from the terminal. Make sure to go all the way up to the start of the errors.
Alternatively, you can provide the latest log files from `../qlik-py-tools/qlik-py-env/core/logs`.
[SSEPlugin.log](https://github.com/nabeel-oz/qlik-py-tools/files/4343855/SSEPlugin.log)


**Error message in Qlik**
Charts showing "Unknown Error"

**Expression or load script used in Qlik**
Pytools.Prophet([Month Start], Sum(Attendances), 'freq=M')

**Environment:**
 - OS [Windows 10]
 - Qlik Sense Desktop
 - SSE Version 7.0

**Additional context**
Add any other context about the problem here.
Looking forward for your response.

Regards,
Tauceef
